<p>&lt;h2 id="budget-planning"&gt;Budget Planning for College Programs&lt;/h2&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;h3&gt;The Real Cost of a Locker Room Project&lt;/h3&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;Here's where programs get into trouble: they look at the per-locker price and think that's the total cost. It's not. Not even close.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;Let me break down what a real project actually costs. Say you're doing 100 lockers at our Varsity tier (\$449 per locker). That's \$44,900 for the lockers themselves. But that's just the beginning.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;You've also got installation—usually \$50-\$150 per locker depending on how complex it is. Are you installing on concrete? Do you need to run electrical? Is the space already prepped? For most projects, figure around \$100 per locker for installation, so that's another \$10,000.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;Then there's shipping. We're in Canada, so shipping to the U.S. runs \$20-\$50 per locker depending on where you are and how many you're ordering. Let's say \$30 per locker average, so that's \$3,000.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;Site preparation is the wild card. Sometimes your space is ready to go. Sometimes you need new flooring, electrical work, HVAC upgrades, or other prep work. We've seen site prep costs range from \$5,000 to \$20,000. Let's use \$10,000 as a middle ground.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;And always, always budget 10-15% for contingency. Something always comes up. Maybe the space measurements were off. Maybe you need extra electrical work. Maybe there's a delay and you need temporary storage. Budget 10% contingency, which is another \$6,790.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;So your total project cost for 100 Varsity tier lockers? \$74,690. Not \$44,900.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&lt;p&gt;I can't tell you how many times we've had programs come to us with a \$50,000 budget thinking they can do 100 lockers, only to realize they need \$75,000. Plan for the full cost upfront, and you'll avoid those awkward conversations with administration when you need more money halfway through the project.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

